From these two considerations therefore, both that he was begotten of God, and that the world was made by him, it is proved that lle is before all things.

This declaration of the Apostle clearly refutes those who deny Christ to have had a personal existence, ὑφιστάμενον, be- fore his incarnation. For how could he have been before all things if he was not before his incarnation? How could he frame all things who was not himself in existence?
